The Amsterdam Tournament is a pre-season &lt;a href="association%20football"&gt;football&lt;/a&gt; tournament held for club teams from around the world, hosted at the &lt;a href="Amsterdam%20ArenA"&gt;Amsterdam ArenA&lt;/a&gt;. The 2002 tournament was contested by &lt;a href="AFC%20Ajax"&gt;Ajax&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="FC%20Barcelona"&gt;Barcelona&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="Manchester%20United%20F.C."&gt;Manchester United&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="Parma%20F.C."&gt;Parma&lt;/a&gt; on 2 August and 4 August 2002. Ajax won the tournament for the second year in a row.
